---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { servicePricingFaqs } from '../../data/pricing';
import PageIntro from '../../components/PageIntro.astro';
import PageCta from '../../components/PageCta.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Restaurant Marketing in Brampton | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Brampton restaurant marketing for South Asian, halal, and fast-growing suburb restaurants. We help Brampton's booming dining scene get found on Google and fill tables."
>

  <main>

    <!-- BREADCRUMB -->
    <Breadcrumb items={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "Locations", href: "/locations/" },
    { label: "Restaurant Marketing Brampton" }
    ]} />

    <!-- HERO -->
    <PageIntro title="Restaurant Marketing in Brampton" description="Brampton's restaurant scene is exploding — new spots opening every week, a community that eats out constantly, and an audience that decides where to go based on what's ranking on Google. Is your restaurant showing up?"  ctaLabel="Book a Free Google Audit" ctaHref="/contact/" />

    <!-- THE LOCAL FOOD SCENE -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="section-label">The Local Food Scene</p><h2>Brampton: Canada's South Asian Dining Capital</h2>
        <p>
          Call it what it is: Brampton has become the South Asian dining capital of Canada. The numbers back it up, but you don't need numbers — just drive along Vodden Street, Queen Street East near Bramalea, or Queen Street West toward the City Centre on a Saturday evening. The parking lots are full, the lineups are real, and the restaurants are churning out some of the best Punjabi, South Indian, Pakistani, and fusion food you'll find anywhere in the country.
        </p>
        <p>
          The halal restaurant strip along Steeles Avenue and Queen Street has become a destination in its own right. Pakistani BBQ spots that open at midnight and stay packed until 3am, Desi-fusion restaurants that blend traditional recipes with Toronto's contemporary plating sensibility, South Indian tiffin houses that have built cult followings through word-of-mouth — Brampton's food scene is legitimately world-class.
        </p>
        <p>
          New restaurants are opening weekly in Brampton, which means competition is intensifying. The restaurants winning in this environment aren't necessarily the best — they're the most visible. They're the ones showing up at the top of Google Maps when someone searches "biryani near me" at 6:30pm on a Tuesday. That's where we come in.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="section-label">What We Do</p><h2>What We Do For Brampton Restaurants</h2>
        <p>
          Marketing for Brampton restaurants requires understanding the community, the competition, and how Brampton diners actually search and discover new places to eat.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Google Maps Positioning:</strong> We optimize your Google Business Profile for the specific searches Brampton customers are making — including high-intent searches like "halal buffet Brampton" and "best karahi Brampton."</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Hyper-Local SEO:</strong> We build content and links targeting neighbourhood-level searches: "South Asian restaurant near Bramalea City Centre," "halal food Queen Street Brampton," and long-tail terms your competitors haven't optimized for yet.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Brampton Food Community Outreach:</strong> We connect you with Brampton-specific food content creators and get your restaurant featured in the Facebook groups, Instagram pages, and WhatsApp communities where Brampton's dining decisions actually happen.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Review Generation System:</strong> We build a consistent, ethical review strategy that grows your Google and Zomato ratings over time — because in a market this competitive, your star rating is often the first thing customers use to filter.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Weekend and Event Targeting:</strong> Brampton's community calendar is packed — cultural events, Celebration Square programming, religious holidays. We time your promotions and ad spend around the moments when people are most actively looking for restaurants like yours.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>→</span>
            <span><strong>Competitor Gap Analysis:</strong> We audit the top-ranking restaurants in your category and neighbourhood and identify exactly where they're weak. Then we build you a strategy to outperform them in those specific areas.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HALAL CALLOUT -->
    <section class="bg-halal-green py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 trg-prose-invert trg-prose">
        <span>Halal Restaurant Community</span>
        <h2>Serving Brampton's Halal Restaurant Community</h2>
        <p>
          Brampton has one of the largest and most active halal dining communities in Canada. The Muslim population here isn't just large — it's engaged, loyal, and highly influential in how dining decisions spread through word-of-mouth and digital communities. A recommendation in the right Brampton halal food Facebook group can send 200 people to your restaurant in a weekend.
        </p>
        <p>
          We know this community. We understand how halal certification affects customer trust, how to position your restaurant within the halal dining ecosystem, and how to reach customers who are specifically filtering for halal options on Google Maps and food delivery platforms.
        </p>
        <p>
          Learn more: <a href="/niche/halal-restaurant-marketing-toronto/">Halal Restaurant Marketing Toronto →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="section-label">Questions</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <p>How much does restaurant marketing cost in Brampton?</p>
          <p style="color: #444;" set:html={servicePricingFaqs.locations} />
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <p>Do you work with restaurants outside Brampton?</p>
          <p>Yes — we serve restaurants across the GTA. Mississauga is our closest partner city to Brampton and we work with many restaurants across both markets. We also serve <a href="/locations/restaurant-marketing-scarborough/">Scarborough</a>, North York, Etobicoke, Vaughan, and Hamilton.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <p>Can you help halal restaurants stand out from Brampton's intense competition?</p>
          <p>That's exactly what we do. The halal dining market in Brampton is massive and growing — which means competition is fierce. We help halal restaurants differentiate through Google positioning, review strategy, and targeted content that speaks to Brampton's Muslim dining community specifically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ALSO SERVING -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="section-label">Also Serving</p><h2>Restaurant Marketing Across the GTA</h2>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/locations/restaurant-marketing-scarborough/">Scarborough</a>
          <a href="/locations/">Mississauga</a>
          <a href="/locations/">Etobicoke</a>
          <a href="/locations/">North York</a>
          <a href="/locations/">Vaughan</a>
          <a href="/locations/">Markham</a>
          <a href="/locations/">Hamilton</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <!-- CTA -->
    <PageCta title="Your Brampton restaurant deserves to be found. Let's make it happen." />

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
